.TH "intel_update_active_dpll" 9 "intel_update_active_dpll" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
intel_update_active_dpll \- update the active DPLL for a CRTC/encoder
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" intel_update_active_dpll
.BI "(struct intel_atomic_state *state "  ","
.BI "struct intel_crtc *crtc "  ","
.BI "struct intel_encoder *encoder "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "state" 12
atomic state
.IP "crtc" 12
the CRTC for which to update the active DPLL
.IP "encoder" 12
encoder determining the type of port DPLL
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Update the active DPLL for the given \fIcrtc\fP/\fIencoder\fP in \fIcrtc\fP's atomic state,
from the port DPLLs reserved previously by \fBintel_reserve_shared_dplls\fP. The
DPLL selected will be based on the current mode of the encoder's port.
